main event: A witness observed an unidentified aerial object near Bethany Beach, Delaware on June 4, 1967.
interesting points: The object appeared as a dark, reddish-orange sphere, like a 'close ranging red gaseous sphere'.
The object moved at an estimated speed of around 150 miles per hour, at an altitude of 1200 feet to 15-20 feet.
The object was observed to suddenly speed up, change brightness, flash or flicker, and disappear and reappear.
The witness reported that the object moved behind a branch of a tree on the beach and also in front of overcast clouds.
The sighting lasted for around 15-20 seconds.
